			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName> <date>3 decr. 5613&#8212;1853</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd. I. Leeser</addressee>&#8212;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Revd Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Tho&#39; our friendship has been dissolved from causes<lb/> at present unnecessary to be recapitulated&#44; yet confident that where<lb/> honor and justice are invoked&#44; you will be found to be the<lb/> last to be swayed by prejudice or party feeling&#44; I address you.<lb/> I am a Candidate for the still vacant office in <placeName>Savannah&#44; Ga.</placeName><lb/> &#40;the <persName>Revd. Mr Rosenfeld</persName> having declined the same&#44; as I learn by a<lb/> letter therefrom this day&#41;. Had my application been forwarded<lb/> with the others from <placeName>Sava.</placeName> To <placeName>New York</placeName> &#38; <placeName>Phila.</placeName> <persName>Dr. De La Motta</persName><lb/> would have been enabled &#40;as he says in his letter&#41; to have made<lb/> personal enquiries. Now it behooves me to address those who<lb/> know me. Having stated in my application that I am<lb/> unfortunately <add>Hebrew</add> and having mentioned your name in<lb/> conjunction with that of <persName>A. Hart Esq</persName> as referees&#44; I would esteem<lb/> it a particular favor if in conjunction or separately as may<lb/> best be deemed advisable&#44; you would address a few lines to<lb/> <persName>Dr. Jacob De La Motta</persName>&#44; Parnass <persName>K. K. Mick</persName><add>&#63;</add>&#39; Israel <placeName>Savanna&#44; Ga</placeName><lb/> and furnish him with such information of the applicant as<lb/> you may deem justly merited.</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">Respectfully Yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">A. J. H. Bernal</persName></p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
